org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.projects

Class DefinitionPriority

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.projects.DefinitionPriority
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<IDefinitionPriority>, IDefinitionPriority

    public final class DefinitionPriority
extends Object
implements IDefinitionPriority
    This class encapsulates information about the priority of definitions defined in a compilation unit. The "priority" of a definition determines whether that definition shadows definitions from other compilation units that have the same qname.

      • setOrder

        public void setOrder(int order)
        Set the order of the definition based on the path list the definition came from. The closer a path is to the beginning of the list the higher its priority.
        Parameters:
        order - the order to set
